  },
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Clinical Setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Usual clinical syndrome: Unexplained fever within a few days postpartum (especially following C-section), post-abortion or post-pelvic surgery; often fever while on appropriate antibiotics for endometritis/pelvic infection.",
        "Complicated by small pulmonary emboli in 2% of cases.",
        "Diagnosis by exclusion; modern imaging may help."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Etiologies"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Streptococcus sp.",
        "Bacteroides sp.",
        "Enterobacteriaceae",
        "Other anaerobic organisms"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Primary Regimens"
    },
    {
      "type": "regimen",
      "regimenData": {
        "intent": "treatment",
        "components": [
          {
            "drug": "Metronidazole",
            "dose": "1 gm loading dose then 0.5 gm q6h or 1 gm IV q12h"
          },
          {
            "drug": "Ceftriaxone",
            "dose": "2 gm",
            "route": "IV",
            "frequency": "q24h",
            "connector": "+"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "regimen",
      "regimenData": {
        "intent": "treatment",
        "components": [
          {
            "drug": "Piperacillin-tazobactam",
            "dose": "4.5 gm",
            "route": "IV",
            "frequency": "(over 4 hr) q8h"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Add heparin anticoagulation to antibiotic regimen; optimal duration is unclear (See Comment)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
